{
  "texts": [
    "This makes the overall file size smaller but does not change the amount of information contained in the data.",
    "In fact, it is part of a family of compressors called ''Entropy Encoders'' [44].",
    "They use a lossless compression method that attempts to approach the lower bound stated by Shannon's ''source coding theorem'', which states that \"any lossless data compression method must have an expected code length greater than or equal to with the entropy of the source\".",
    "Claude Shannon just before he died, wrote the very interesting ''Entropy and Redundancy in English'' which talks about how he calculated that the letters in the English language have about 2.62 bits of information per letter [45].",
    "Given all the above, it should by now be evident that there is a ''ceiling'' of the Machine Learning process which can never exceed the 100% of the information contained within the data set and is being transferred in the model."
  ]
}